ðŸ“Œ Factorial Calculator in Java
This Java program calculates the factorial of a given non-negative integer entered by the user. 
It uses a simple for loop to compute the factorial and handles invalid (negative) inputs gracefully.


import java.util.*;
public class Factorial {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		int n = sc.nextInt();
		if(n<0) {
			System.out.println("Factorial cannot be done for negative numbers");
		}
		else {
			int fact = 1;
			for(int i=1;i<=n;i++) {
				fact = fact*i;
			}
			System.out.println("Factorial of given number is: "+fact);
			
		}
		
	}

}


ðŸ”§ Features:
Takes user input using Scanner

Checks for negative input and shows an error message

Calculates factorial using iterative approach

Displays the result in a user-friendly message
